[
    {
        "content": "<p>As a computer science undergraduate with close to 1 year of experience with Coq who would like to get started with Lean for doing \"fashionable mathematics\" (as <a href=\"https://xenaproject.wordpress.com/2020/02/09/where-is-the-fashionable-mathematics/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://xenaproject.wordpress.com/2020/02/09/where-is-the-fashionable-mathematics/\">Kevin Buzzard puts it</a>) at the undergraduate level, what tutorial would you recommend?</p>",
        "id": 188355359,
        "sender_full_name": "Donald Sebastian Leung",
        "timestamp": 1581920375
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You'll breeze through the natural number game</p>",
        "id": 188355420,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1581920457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But it will teach you the system</p>",
        "id": 188355436,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1581920485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then there's the book \"Theorem proving in Lean\"</p>",
        "id": 188355447,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1581920508
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And the <code>docs/</code> folder in the mathlib repo</p>",
        "id": 188355451,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1581920520
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And finally, just pick a topic you like, and start working on it. Make sure to show your files here and ask for feedback.</p>",
        "id": 188355508,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1581920572
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's also the lecture notes to the course Logical Verification in Lean: <a href=\"https://lean-forward.github.io/logical-verification/2019/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://lean-forward.github.io/logical-verification/2019/\">https://lean-forward.github.io/logical-verification/2019/</a></p>",
        "id": 188355714,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryan Gin-ge Chen",
        "timestamp": 1581920963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for your recommendations <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span> Since I've done the natural number game before, Theorem Proving in Lean sounds like a good next step.</p>",
        "id": 188361073,
        "sender_full_name": "Donald Sebastian Leung",
        "timestamp": 1581929431
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Especially the <code>mathlib/docs/extras</code> is really useful. I think it is what took me from \"knows how to fill in a sorry\" to \"can deal with most problems themselves\".</p>",
        "id": 188364824,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton Lorenzen",
        "timestamp": 1581933082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And <code>https://leanprover.github.io/reference/tactics.html</code> is a nice encyclopedia of builtin tactics</p>",
        "id": 188364928,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton Lorenzen",
        "timestamp": 1581933148
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also clone the <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/tutorials\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/tutorials\">tutorial project</a> or use its <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/lean-web-editor/#url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fleanprover-community%2Ftutorials%2Fmaster%2Fsrc%2Ffirst_proofs.lean\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/lean-web-editor/#url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fleanprover-community%2Ftutorials%2Fmaster%2Fsrc%2Ffirst_proofs.lean\">only file so far</a> online if you are patient enough.</p>",
        "id": 188365062,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1581933278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, we should bump the Lean/mathlib version on the tutorial.</p>",
